txt.en: Ufúrzrak Orcs and thrug-hai can be found at Muru Azog, before the East-gate of Nud-mekhem at Azanulbizar.\n\nYou should defeat the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog.
Ufúrzrak Orcs and thrug-hai can be found at Muru Azog, before the East-gate of Nud-mekhem at Azanulbizar.\n\nYou should defeat the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog.
You have defeated many Orcs of the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog.
Although the halls of Khazad-dûm still teem with Orcs, you have done much to thin the numbers of the Ufúrzrak and weaken Azog's hold on Azanulbizar.
The Orcs of the Ufúrzrak, Azog's clan, dwell within and without the old kingdom of Khazad-dûm.

Defeat the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog

Encamped in the very shadows of Nud-mekhem, the East-gate, the Orcs of the Ufúrzrak have laid claim to Khazad-dûm in the name of their chieftain, Azog. Determined to keep hold of their would-be realm, countless Orcs of the Ufúrzrak, including the vicious and powerful thrug-hai, have gathered before the East-gate.\n\nYou should defeat the Orcs and thrug-hai of the Ufúrzrak at Muru Azog.
